Main effect

#simulated e1-solutions
de1<-read.csv("data/esolution1_no_mental.csv")
#simulated e2-solutions
de2<-read.csv("data/esolution2_no_mental.csv")
#simulated e1-control
dc1<-read.csv("data/esolution_control1_no_mental.csv")
#simulated e2-control
dc2<-read.csv("data/esolution_control2_no_mental.csv")

#delete X (artefact from csv saving)
de1$X<-de2$X<-dc1$X<-dc2$X<-NULL

#generate usable files
de1<-data.frame(probs=as.vector(t(de1)), lrate=rep(seq(0, 0, 0.05), 1), alpha=rep(1:1, each=1))
de2<-data.frame(probs=as.vector(t(de2)), lrate=rep(seq(0, 0, 0.05), 1), alpha=rep(1:1, each=1))
dc1<-data.frame(probs=as.vector(t(dc1)), lrate=rep(seq(0, 0, 0.05), 1), alpha=rep(1:1, each=1))
dc2<-data.frame(probs=as.vector(t(dc2)), lrate=rep(seq(0, 0, 0.05), 1), alpha=rep(1:1, each=1))

#read in 
d<-read.csv("data/luchinsmain.csv")
d<-subset(d, Group != 'DBB')

Reconstructed plot

#build a model to predict E1
m<-glm(E1~Group, data=d, family="binomial")

#predict probs and SEs
pred<-predict(m, newdata = data.frame(Group=c('Control', 'Plain')), type="response", se.fit=TRUE)

#get percentages
dp1<-data.frame(p=100*pred$fit+1, se=100*pred$se.fit, Group=c('Control', 'Plain'))

#fit to E2
m<-glm(E2~Group, data=d, family="binomial")
#predict probs and SEs
pred<-predict(m, newdata = data.frame(Group=c('Control', 'Plain')), type="response", se.fit=TRUE)

#get percentages (we add 1 to make line visible)
dp2<-data.frame(p=100*pred$fit+1, se=100*pred$se.fit, Group=c('Control','Plain'))

#bind together
dp<-rbind(dp1, dp2)

#recode responses names for nicer plotting
dp$response<-rep(c("C1/C2", "C3/C4"), each=2)

#change name of Group
dp$Group<-ifelse(dp$Group=='Plain', 'Experiment', 'Control')
#relevel
dp$Group<-factor(dp$Group, levels=c('Experiment', 'Control'))

#color palette
cbPalette <- c("#009E73", "#F0E442")

#limits with 95% CIs
limits <- aes(ymax = p + 1.96*se, ymin=p - 1.96*se)

#plot
p1 <- ggplot(dp, aes(y=p, x=Group, fill=Group)) + 
  #bars
  geom_bar(position="dodge", stat="identity")+
  #error bars
  geom_errorbar(limits, position="dodge", width=0.1)+
  #points
  geom_point(size=1)+
  #color
  scale_fill_manual(values = c(cbPalette))+
  #theme
  theme_minimal() +
  #limits
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0,100), expand = c(0, 0)) +
  #two facets
  facet_wrap(~response)+
  #labs
  xlab("Condition")+
  ylab("% E-solutions")+
  #title
  ggtitle("a) Reconstructed Effect")+
  #adjust text size
  theme(text = element_text(size=12,  family="sans"),
        axis.text.x = element_text(size = 8))+
  #no legend
  theme(legend.position = "none")
p1

Simulated plot

dd<-rbind(subset(de1, lrate==0.0 & alpha==1), 
          subset(de2, lrate==0.0 & alpha==1),
          subset(dc1, lrate==0.0 & alpha==1), 
          subset(dc2, lrate==0.0 & alpha==1))

#reconstructed behavioral data
d<-read.csv("data/einstellungsize.csv")

#simulated data
eshort1<-read.csv("data/e1short_no_mental.csv")
eshort2<-read.csv("data/e2short_no_mental.csv")
elong1<-read.csv("data/e1long_no_mental.csv")
elong2<-read.csv("data/e2long_no_mental.csv")

#delete X since it's an artefact
eshort1$X<-eshort2$X<-elong1$X<-elong2$X<-NULL

#get simulated data to usable format
eshort1<-data.frame(probs=as.vector(t(eshort1)), lrate=rep(seq(0, 0, 0.05), 1), alpha=rep(1:1, each=1))
eshort2<-data.frame(probs=as.vector(t(eshort2)), lrate=rep(seq(0, 0, 0.05), 1), alpha=rep(1:1, each=1))
elong1<-data.frame(probs=as.vector(t(elong1)), lrate=rep(seq(0, 0, 0.05), 1), alpha=rep(1:1, each=1))
elong2<-data.frame(probs=as.vector(t(elong2)), lrate=rep(seq(0, 0, 0.05), 1), alpha=rep(1:1, each=1))

Reconstructed plot

#using SE here becaus GLM struggles with only 1s as observations
se<-function(x){sd(x)/sqrt(length(x))}

#summarize behavioral data for E1
dd1<-ddply(d, ~Tasks, summarize, p=mean(E1*100), se=se(E1*100))

              type="response", se.fit=TRUE)

dp<-data.frame(mu=100*pred$fit+1, se=100*pred$se.fit, 
               Group=1:4)

              type="response", se.fit=TRUE)

               Group=1:4)
